Present law (R.S. 36:508.6(C)) requires the DOTD enact comprehensive, dept.-wide.
reforms of the access permit process to include the police, administrative code, engineering
directives and standards manual, and online application processes by June 30, 2026.
Proposed law changes the deadline for the availability of the online application process from
June 30, 2026 to June 30, 2027.
Present law (R.S. 36:508.6(D)) requires the DOTD to modernize and reform project
development and execution across the entire dept. to stabilize letting and to remit payments
to vendors and contractors on a bi-monthly basis, consistent with the terms of its contracts,
no later than June 30, 2026.
Proposed law changes the deadline for the DOTD to modernize and reform project
development from June 30, 2026 to June 30, 2027.
Effective upon signature of the governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
